Package tsp

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ant
    A Ant is used to transverse a TSPGraph in order to find a solution to the Traveling Salesman Problem, that is, the Hamiltonian Cycle wth less cost.
    AntEvent
    AntEvent is a Event that moves a ant to the next node, the time is based on an exponential distribuiton with mean value proportional to the weight of the next node.
    EvaporationEvent
    EvaporationEvent is a Event that evaporates pheromones from a edge of a TSPGraph the time is based on an exponential distribuiton with mean value proportional to the eta of the TSPGRaph
    Event
    A Event is a general class for events to be simulated on the PEC.
    Main  
    ObservationEvent
    ObservationEvent is a Event that prints to the terminal the result of observations of the system, showing the current time of the simulation, the number of AntEvents and EvaporationEvents simulated so far and the shortest Hamiltonian Cycle found so far by every Ant.
    TSPGraph
    The TSPGraph class extends the UndirectedGraph class.
